    "body": "### Problem\n\nMessage area is not cleared properly when cmd height is changed.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nrun: `nvim --clean -u min.vim`\r\nenter `:call T(10) | resize +5<cr>`\r\nmin.vim:  \r\n```vim\r\nfunction! T(h)\r\n  let i = 0\r\n  let s = 'xx'\r\n  while i < a:h\r\n    echo s\r\n    let s = s .. 'xx'\r\n    let i = i + 1\r\n  endwhile\r\nendfunction\r\n\r\nset ch=20\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nMessage area is properly cleared.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1259+gc0f4d6001-dirty Build type: Debug LuaJIT 2.1.1695653777\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.12.2 (9d9982df)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nrepo",
